               <head>Miscellaneous Sufi works</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Collection of three Sufi biographical and epistolary works, endorsed on a flyleaf as <title>Maktūbāt-i mukarrar-i Ḥaz̤rat-i Mujaddid</title>. Heavily annotated in parts. Not dated. Transcribed by multiple hands in rough shikastah, often illegible. Edges cropped. Detached binding; marbled paper on exterior; descriptive labels missing; fragile. 
                  </summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85089787" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_960-item1">
                     <locus from="1" to="122v">ff. 1-122v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled account of the Naqshbandī leader, <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657162.0x000001 viaf_32839461" role="subject">Shaykh Aḥmad Sihrindī (usually Sarhindī), titled Mujaddid-i Alf-i S̲ānī</persName>, whose spiritual genealogy is traced back to the <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656957.0x000001 viaf_27868234" role="subject">Caliph ʿUmar ibn al-Khattā</persName>b. This is followed by a number of letters, mainly Sufi in subject matter. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008118219 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008118218" n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_960-item2">
                     <locus from="126" to="139v">ff. 126-139v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled disquisition on the esoteric significance of the names of God. </p>
                        <p>Author not identified. </p>
                        <p>Not dated. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2009125966" n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_960-item3">
                     <locus from="140r" to="156v">ff. 140r-156v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Collection of miscellaneous letters, theological compositions and poems (manqabat or qaṣīdah) on Naqshbandī Sūfī themes, with occasional blank pages separating compositions </p>
                        <p>Not dated. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
